46 template <typename Left, typename Right, typename Result>
47 struct EngineTrait<MultEngine<Left, Right, Result> > {
48  static_assert(
49  std::is_same<typename EngineTrait<Left>::policy,
50  typename EngineTrait<Right>::policy>::value,
51  "The left- and right-hand expressions must use the same policy class");
52 
53  // Argument typedefs
54  typedef Left left_type;
55  typedef Right right_type;
56 
57  // Operational typedefs
58  typedef TiledArray::detail::Mult<
59  Result, typename EngineTrait<Left>::eval_type,
60  typename EngineTrait<Right>::eval_type, EngineTrait<Left>::consumable,
61  EngineTrait<Right>::consumable>
62  op_base_type;
63  typedef TiledArray::detail::BinaryWrapper<op_base_type>
64  op_type;
65  typedef typename op_type::result_type value_type;
66  typedef typename eval_trait<value_type>::type
67  eval_type;
68  typedef typename TiledArray::detail::numeric_type<value_type>::type
69  scalar_type;
70  typedef typename Left::policy policy;
71  typedef TiledArray::detail::DistEval<value_type, policy>
72  dist_eval_type;
73 
74  // Meta data typedefs
75  typedef typename policy::size_type size_type;
76  typedef typename policy::trange_type trange_type;
77  typedef typename policy::shape_type shape_type;
78  typedef typename policy::pmap_interface
79  pmap_interface;
80 
81  static constexpr bool consumable = is_consumable_tile<eval_type>::value;
82  static constexpr unsigned int leaves =
83  EngineTrait<Left>::leaves + EngineTrait<Right>::leaves;
84 };

191 
197  void perm_vars(const VariableList& target_vars) {
198  if (contract_)
199  ContEngine_::perm_vars(target_vars);
200  else {
201  BinaryEngine_::perm_vars(target_vars);
202  }
203  }
204 
206 
208  void init_vars(const VariableList& target_vars) {
209  BinaryEngine_::left_.init_vars();
210  BinaryEngine_::right_.init_vars();
211 
212  // it's either pure Hadamard (detect by checking that left arg's and
213  // target's vars are the "same") or contraction
214  // TODO add mixed Hadamard+contraction
215  if (BinaryEngine_::left_.vars().is_permutation(target_vars)) {
216  TA_ASSERT(BinaryEngine_::left_.vars().is_permutation(
217  BinaryEngine_::right_.vars()));
218  BinaryEngine_::perm_vars(target_vars);
219  } else {
220  contract_ = true;
221  ContEngine_::init_vars();
222  ContEngine_::perm_vars(target_vars);
223  }
224  }
225 
227  void init_vars() {
228  BinaryEngine_::left_.init_vars();
229  BinaryEngine_::right_.init_vars();
230 
231  if (BinaryEngine_::left_.vars().is_permutation(
232  BinaryEngine_::right_.vars())) {
233  if (left_type::leaves <= right_type::leaves)
234  ExprEngine_::vars_ = BinaryEngine_::left_.vars();
235  else
236  ExprEngine_::vars_ = BinaryEngine_::right_.vars();
237  } else {
238  contract_ = true;
239  ContEngine_::init_vars();
240  }
241  }
242 
244 
248  void init_struct(const VariableList& target_vars) {
249  if (contract_)
250  ContEngine_::init_struct(target_vars);
251  else
252  BinaryEngine_::init_struct(target_vars);
253  }
254

261  void init_distribution(World* world, std::shared_ptr<pmap_interface> pmap) {

266  }
